column3: $Drive caromed off Holloway's pitching hand to Haney. Holloway was unable to resume pitching.
$Veach was knocked out when he ran into an iron post guarding temporary seats.  He recovered and resumed.
$Myatt threw to 2B getting Heilmann in a rundown. Heilmann was called out for running out of line. Lutzke threw wild to 1B trying to get Pratt who then was cut down trying for 3B.
$Heilmann was ejected by Ump Ormsby for protesting the decision at the plate.
$Heilmann out serving a 1-game suspension, the aftermath of his argument with Ump Ormsby on 5/2/23.
$Cobb spiked Scott on the play at 2B. Jones wrenched his ankle as he slid home and had to be carried off field.

$Falk was hit on the back of head by a fast pitch and fell to the ground, but revived and took 1B.  He apparently suffered no ill-effects from the beaning as he displayed considerable pep around 1B.

$Throw to 3B bounded past Haney, who covered the bag.  As Severeid slid into 3B he bumped Haney.  Haney then grabbed Severeid by the leg.  They argued and Ump Evans stepped in to prevent blows, then waved Severeid home.

$Gardner was safe as Pillette juggled Blue's throw to 1B. When Gardner walked off the bag, Pillette threw to Haney who tagged him out. It's not clear if Gardner thought he was out and left the bag, or if he fell victim to the hidden ball trick
